'''Emmanuel Janssen''' (1879-1955) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman, who founded the [[Union Chimique Belge]] (UCB) in Brussels, Belgium, in 1928. UCB was one of the first companies in the world to distill ammonia from coal.<ref>http://www.ucb.com/about-ucb/history</ref>

