{{Expand German|Johann Georg Ehrlich|date=February 2011}}
'''Johann Georg Ehrlich''' (13 October 1676 – 8 February 1743) was a German merchant and town councillor from [[Dresden]].

Ehrlich was born in {{Interlanguage link multi|Hennersdorf (Dippoldiswalde)|de|3=Hennersdorf (Dippoldiswalde)|lt=Hennersdorf}} near [[Frauenstein, Saxony|Frauenstein]].  As well as his public service in Dresden, he founded the eponymous [[Ehrlichsches Gestift]].  He died in Dresden, aged 66.


