{{Infobox University | name = University of Haripur | image = UOH-Logo.jpeg | image_size = 150 px | established = 2008 | type = [[Public university|Public]] | chancellor = [[Governor of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] | vice_chancellor = Prof. Dr. Abid Fareed<ref>http://www.uoh.edu.pk/administration.php?page=vice-chancellor-office</ref> | city = [[Haripur, Pakistan|Haripur]] | state = [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] | country = [[Pakistan]]{{flagicon|Pakistan}} | nickname = UOH | academic staff = | students = | accreditation = | affiliations = [[Higher Education Commission (Pakistan)]] | website = {{URL|uoh.edu.pk}} }}
The '''University of Haripur (UOH)''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|یونیورسٹی آف ہری پور}}}}) is a [[public university]] situated in [[Haripur, Pakistan|Haripur]], [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]], [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=HEC Recognise Colleges and Universities|url=http://www.hec.gov.pk/english/universities/Documents/New_Affiliation%20data%20list.pdf|website=www.hec.gov.pk|accessdate=18 September 2017|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=HEC announces university ranking|url=http://nation.com.pk/lahore/06-Jul-2013/hec-announces-university-ranking|website=The Nation|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=K-P picks VCs for nine universities - The Express Tribune|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1391735/phc-stay-order-ignored-k-p-picks-vcs-nine-universities/|website=The Express Tribune|accessdate=9 October 2017|date=24 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Expo-2016 to prove great milestone in promoting social sciences|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/96724-Expo-2016-to-prove-great-milestone-in-promoting-social-sciences|website=www.thenews.com.pk|accessdate=9 October 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Report|first1=Bureau|title=Appointment of nine VCs notified|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1338438|website=DAWN.COM|accessdate=9 October 2017|date=9 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Varsity announces fee waiver for Baloch students|url=http://nation.com.pk/islamabad/05-Sep-2015/varsity-announces-fee-waiver-for-baloch-students|website=The Nation|accessdate=9 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Report|first1=Bureau|title=KP governor to contact PM over funds for universities|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1021463|website=DAWN.COM|accessdate=9 October 2017|date=29 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=University of Haripur|url=http://www.uoh.edu.pk/|website=www.uoh.edu.pk|accessdate=18 September 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite web|title=Five public sector universities in KP functioning without VCs|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/181751-Five-public-sector-universities-in-KP-functioning-without-VCs|website=www.thenews.com.pk|accessdate=9 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>
== Overview == The university premises is spread over an area of 236 Kanals on the premises of once factory of Rosin and Turpentine.
== History == UOH was established in March 2008 as a Haripur campus of [[Hazara University]]. The campus was upgraded to full-fledged University of Haripur (UOH) in 2012 by the [[Government of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Newspaper|first1=From the|title=NEWS IN BRIEF - Approval of upgrading sub-campus of the Hazara University in Haripur to university level|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/705005|website=DAWN.COM|accessdate=9 October 2017|date=23 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=University of Haripur|url=https://www.uoh.edu.pk/page.php?page=about-us|website=www.uoh.edu.pk|accessdate=9 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>
